 ('375', '380', 'en_us', 'Greg Kiskadden', NULL, 'Executive Vice President - WhiteSpace Creative', '', '', '<p>Executive Vice President Greg Kiskadden oversees WhiteSpace Creative new business development. He draws from his rich leadership background to foster key relationships with prospective clients from a diverse body of industries, such as service, manufacturing, logistics, healthcare and higher education. He also supports comprehensive agency operations, including spearheading workflow and scheduling improvements and assisting in overall agency integration.</p><p>A member of WhiteSpace since 1996, Greg has transitioned from a designer and developer to account supervisor and agency executive vice president. Experience in these varied roles has enabled Greg to combine his talents in developing integrated communication programs with extensive client service and sales expertise. It also has allowed him to view projects from a unique perspective  one that blends strategic marketing and tactical execution to support business goals.</p><p>Prior to WhiteSpace, Greg worked at The Little Tikes Company, a division of Rubbermaid in Hudson, Ohio, where he helped develop product literature for domestic and international sales, print collateral and advertising material. A Kent State graduate, he earned a BA in visual communications with a concentration in illustration and art history. Greg currently serves on the Habitat for Humanity public relations and communications board, as well as on the professional advisory board of IdeaBase, a Kent State University student-run marketing communications firm in Kent, Ohio.</p><p>Greg is an avid runner and, in addition to competing in the Akron and Nashville half-marathons, he coaches cross country for St. Patrick School in Kent, Ohio. He enjoys travel and has journeyed to Italy, Belize, Trinidad, Tobago and Puerto Rico. Greg lives in Kent with his wife and two daughters.</p>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Kiskadden', 'Greg', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-05 18:30:52', '2016-01-22 18:02:12', 'c7181f5d-2fab-44c8-84a2-2516dc4d632e'),
 ('376', '381', 'en_us', 'Greg Thomas', NULL, 'Creative Director - Point to Point', '', '', '<p>Greg has spent more than 25 years managing the creative process and&nbsp;coaching creative teams to help businesses be more successful. As a writer,&nbsp;creative director, account director and advertising agency manager, Greg has&nbsp;helped clients such as Ameritech, McDonalds, Goodyear, Sherwin Williams,&nbsp;FirstEnergy, Parker Hannifin, White Castle and many others manage their brands&nbsp;successfully. The work produced by the teams and agencies he has led has&nbsp;been showcased in numerous national and international competitions and trade&nbsp;journals.</p><p>As Partner/ Creative Director at Point to Point, Greg guides the creative thinking&nbsp;of the agency and its clients and manages the agencys creative staff.</p><p>Greg has been very involved in education as well.&nbsp;As an adjunct faculty member&nbsp;and Practitioner in Residence at Kent State University, he helped develop a&nbsp;creative curriculum in the Advertising program and guided the launch and first&nbsp;year of IdeaBase, the student-run integrated marketing communications&nbsp;firm. He has also guest lectured on the topic of creativity in the Executive MBA&nbsp;program at Cleveland States Nance College of Business. Greg holds bachelors&nbsp;degrees in English and Education from Kent State.</p>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Thomas', 'Greg', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-05 18:33:07', '2016-01-22 18:02:12', '6248efc5-cd91-49e9-a210-7e02baf0f31d'),
