 ('224', '380', '3', '87', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"87\",\"title\":\"Greg Kiskadden\",\"slug\":\"greg-kiskadden\",\"postDate\":1452018651,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"<p>Executive Vice President Greg Kiskadden oversees WhiteSpace Creative new business development. He draws from his rich leadership background to foster key relationships with prospective clients from a diverse body of industries, such as service, manufacturing, logistics, healthcare and higher education. He also supports comprehensive agency operations, including spearheading workflow and scheduling improvements and assisting in overall agency integration.<\\/p><p>A member of WhiteSpace since 1996, Greg has transitioned from a designer and developer to account supervisor and agency executive vice president. Experience in these varied roles has enabled Greg to combine his talents in developing integrated communication programs with extensive client service and sales expertise. It also has allowed him to view projects from a unique perspective \\u2013 one that blends strategic marketing and tactical execution to support business goals.<\\/p><p>Prior to WhiteSpace, Greg worked at The Little Tikes Company, a division of Rubbermaid in Hudson, Ohio, where he helped develop product literature for domestic and international sales, print collateral and advertising material. A Kent State graduate, he earned a BA in visual communications with a concentration in illustration and art history. Greg currently serves on the Habitat for Humanity public relations and communications board, as well as on the professional advisory board of IdeaBase, a Kent State University student-run marketing communications firm in Kent, Ohio.<\\/p><p>Greg is an avid runner and, in addition to competing in the Akron and Nashville half-marathons, he coaches cross country for St. Patrick School in Kent, Ohio. He enjoys travel and has journeyed to Italy, Belize, Trinidad, Tobago and Puerto Rico. Greg lives in Kent with his wife and two daughters.<\\/p>\",\"77\":\"\",\"4\":\"\",\"115\":\"Greg\",\"7\":\"\",\"26\":[\"7\"],\"3\":\"Executive Vice President - WhiteSpace Creative\",\"114\":\"Kiskadden\",\"5\":\"\",\"27\":[\"379\"],\"89\":\"\"}}', '2016-01-05 18:30:52', '2016-01-05 18:30:52', 'e23da502-d319-4b40-9b15-27ca122bd839'),
 ('225', '381', '3', '87', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"87\",\"title\":\"Greg Thomas\",\"slug\":\"greg-thomas\",\"postDate\":1452018787,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"<p>Greg has spent more than 25 years managing the creative process and&nbsp;coaching creative teams to help businesses be more successful. As a writer,&nbsp;creative director, account director and advertising agency manager, Greg has&nbsp;helped clients such as Ameritech, McDonald\\u2019s, Goodyear, Sherwin Williams,&nbsp;FirstEnergy, Parker Hannifin, White Castle and many others manage their brands&nbsp;successfully. The work produced by the teams and agencies he has led has&nbsp;been showcased in numerous national and international competitions and trade&nbsp;journals.<\\/p><p>As Partner\\/ Creative Director at Point to Point, Greg guides the creative thinking&nbsp;of the agency and its clients and manages the agency\\u2019s creative staff.<\\/p><p>Greg has been very involved in education as well.&nbsp;As an adjunct faculty member&nbsp;and Practitioner in Residence at Kent State University, he helped develop a&nbsp;creative curriculum in the Advertising program and guided the launch and first&nbsp;year of IdeaBase, the student-run integrated marketing communications&nbsp;firm. He has also guest lectured on the topic of creativity in the Executive MBA&nbsp;program at Cleveland State\\u2019s Nance College of Business. Greg holds bachelor\\u2019s&nbsp;degrees in English and Education from Kent State.<\\/p>\",\"77\":\"\",\"4\":\"\",\"115\":\"Greg\",\"7\":\"\",\"26\":[\"7\"],\"3\":\"Creative Director - Point to Point\",\"114\":\"Thomas\",\"5\":\"\",\"27\":\"\",\"89\":\"\"}}', '2016-01-05 18:33:08', '2016-01-05 18:33:08', '8ed37f33-c130-4c81-882d-6354d13b4976'),
 ('226', '382', '3', '87', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"87\",\"title\":\"Steve Lageson\",\"slug\":\"steve-lageson\",\"postDate\":1452019054,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"\",\"77\":\"\",\"4\":\"\",\"115\":\"Steve\",\"7\":\"\",\"26\":[\"7\"],\"3\":\"Associate Creative Director - Wyse Advertising\",\"114\":\"Lageson\",\"5\":\"\",\"27\":\"\",\"89\":\"\"}}', '2016-01-05 18:37:34', '2016-01-05 18:37:34', 'cbd6e6a4-eaa5-4806-af5e-6000978e958b'),
 ('227', '384', '3', '87', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"87\",\"title\":\"Danielle Coombs, Ph.D.\",\"slug\":\"danielle-coombs-ph-d\",\"postDate\":1452019847,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"<p>Dr. Coombs is an Assistant Professor in the School of Journalism and Mass Communication at Kent State University. In addition to this position, she is the founder and principal of Sarver Research, a Cleveland-based market research firm. Prior to returning to northeastern Ohio, Dr. Coombs served as a senior research manager for Insight Research Group in New York City. While at Insight, she specialized in uncovering consumer insights in order to inform advertising campaigns, product design, and brand strategies for numerous prominent brands from a variety of industries including television, retail, non-profits, and consumer packaged goods. In 2007, she completed her Ph.D. in Mass Communication and Public Affairs from the Manship School of Communication at Louisiana State University. Her dissertation examined the political effects of late night television comedy. She also holds a master\\u2019s degree in international mass communication and a bachelor\\u2019s degree in media studies, both from the School of Telecommunications at Ohio University.<\\/p>\",\"77\":\"\",\"4\":\"\",\"115\":\"Danielle\",\"7\":\"\",\"26\":[\"8\"],\"3\":\"Assistant Professor, Journalism & Mass Communication\",\"114\":\"Coombs, Ph.D.\",\"5\":\"\",\"27\":[\"383\"],\"89\":\"\"}}', '2016-01-05 18:50:48', '2016-01-05 18:50:48', 'b847a88e-c92f-4e27-bd9c-55b9d87a0142'),
 ('228', '385', '3', '87', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"87\",\"title\":\"David Robins, Ph.D.\",\"slug\":\"david-robins-ph-d\",\"postDate\":1452019897,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"\",\"77\":\"\",\"4\":\"\",\"115\":\"\",\"7\":\"\",\"26\":\"\",\"3\":\"\",\"114\":\"\",\"5\":\"\",\"27\":\"\",\"89\":\"\"}}', '2016-01-05 18:51:38', '2016-01-05 18:51:38', '22de2ddc-65ca-457d-a356-2759c21b1bfe'),
 ('229', '385', '3', '87', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"87\",\"title\":\"David Robins, Ph.D.\",\"slug\":\"david-robins-ph-d\",\"postDate\":1452019860,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"6\":\"<p>Dr. Robins is an Associate Professor at Kent State University and holds a Ph.D. in Information Science from the University of North Texas. His research foci are information architecture, visual explanations of complex constructs, and user interaction with information systems. Much of his published work concerns users\\u2019 interaction with information seeking structures. He has developed courses in information technologies, information architecture and knowledge management which integrate theory with real world application. Dr. Robins has conducted presentations in the US, Mexico and Denmark.<\\/p>\",\"77\":\"\",\"4\":\"\",\"115\":\"David\",\"7\":\"\",\"26\":[\"8\"],\"3\":\"Full Professor, Information and Knowledge Management\",\"114\":\"Robins, Ph.D.\",\"5\":\"\",\"27\":[\"386\"],\"89\":\"\"}}', '2016-01-05 18:56:59', '2016-01-05 18:56:59', '0dcafee9-83b0-4597-8373-32ff9bf149a0'),
 ('230', '388', '3', '87', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"87\",\"title\":\"Jillian Coorey\",\"slug\":\"jillian-coorey\",\"postDate\":1452020353,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"<p>Jillian Coorey is an Assistant Professor in the School of Visual Communication Design at Kent State University. Prior to coming to Kent, Jillian spent five years working in Chicago as a designer for various companies, in addition to managing freelance clientele. As a designer, she strives to create thoughtful and innovative solutions that combine conceptual and creative thinking. Jillian received her MFA in Graphic Design from the University of Illinois at Chicago and her BFA in Graphic Design from The State University of New York at Fredonia. She has also studied in Basel, Switzerland at The Basel School of Design. Her thesis research involved dance and design, creating work that challenges and informs the dimensional experience of movement, time and space.<\\/p>\",\"77\":\"\",\"4\":\"\",\"115\":\"Jillian\",\"7\":\"\",\"26\":[\"8\"],\"3\":\"Assistant Professor, Visual Communication Design\",\"114\":\"Coorey\",\"5\":\"\",\"27\":[\"387\"],\"89\":\"\"}}', '2016-01-05 18:59:13', '2016-01-05 18:59:13', '0207a2bb-5194-4208-a009-b3513df7e346'),
 ('231', '390', '3', '87', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"87\",\"title\":\"Pamela Grimm, Ph.D.\",\"slug\":\"pamela-grimm-ph-d\",\"postDate\":1452020947,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"<p>Dr. Grimm joined Kent State University in 1992 as an Associate Professor. She is currently an Associate Professor and Chair of the Department of Marketing and Entrepreneurship. She worked in Advertising before pursuing and completing her doctorate in Marketing at the State University of New York at Buffalo. Her research interests are in consumer behavior, specifically motivation and information search, advertising and celebrity endorsements. Dr. Grimm has been a participant in the Advertising Education Foundation\\u2019s Faculty Internship program and has received several teaching awards. Courses she has taught include Marketing, Consumer Behavior, Advertising and Internet Marketing at the Undergraduate level and Marketing Management at the Graduate level. Dr. Grimm has also been a faculty member in the Executive MBA program, teaching the International Business Experience.<\\/p>\",\"77\":\"\",\"4\":\"\",\"115\":\"Pamela\",\"7\":\"\",\"26\":[\"8\"],\"3\":\"Associate Professor, Marketing Chair\",\"114\":\"Grimm, Ph.D.\",\"5\":\"\",\"27\":[\"389\"],\"89\":\"\"}}', '2016-01-05 19:09:07', '2016-01-05 19:09:07', 'be7a56ea-394d-4fb7-a214-d78492521603'),
 ('232', '392', '3', '87', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"87\",\"title\":\"Paul Haridakis, Ph.D.\",\"slug\":\"paul-haridakis-ph-d\",\"postDate\":1452021075,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"<p>Dr. Haridakis is a full Professor at Kent State University. He completed his doctorate at Kent State University and holds a J.D. and Bachelor of the Arts from the University of Akron. He conducts research in media uses and effects, law, public policy, new communication technologies, and media ethics. His recent work has focused on First Amendment issues related to the regulation of content in various media such as the Internet and television. He teaches courses in Free Speech, Research Methods, Communication Process, and Senior Seminar. He also is a practicing lawyer.<\\/p>\",\"77\":\"\",\"4\":\"\",\"115\":\"Paul\",\"7\":\"\",\"26\":[\"8\"],\"3\":\"Full Professor, Director of Communication Studies\",\"114\":\"Haridakis, Ph.D.\",\"5\":\"\",\"27\":[\"391\"],\"89\":\"\"}}', '2016-01-05 19:11:16', '2016-01-05 19:11:16', 'c0c41f6d-696e-4d62-9f21-0fb17ef704d6'),
 ('233', '394', '3', '87', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"87\",\"title\":\"Valora Renicker\",\"slug\":\"valora-renicker\",\"postDate\":1452021335,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"<p>Valora received her MFA in Graphic Design from Kent State University and a BFA in Graphic Design and Art Education from the University of Akron. Her background includes experience in the design field and teaching art in the public schools. Valora is an Assistant Professor in the School of Visual Communication Design (VCD) at Kent State University where she has taught course in typography, formal and conceptual design development, 3D graphic design and computer software. She is the Creative Director of&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.kent.edu\\/glyphix\\\">Glyphix<\\/a>, an award-winning student-staffed design studio within the School of VCD, where she instructs both undergraduate and graduate level students in the real-world implementation of design practices and production.<\\/p>\",\"77\":\"\",\"4\":\"\",\"115\":\"Valora\",\"7\":\"\",\"26\":[\"8\"],\"3\":\"Assistant Professor, Visual Communication Design and Creative Director, Glyphix Design Studio\",\"114\":\"Renicker\",\"5\":\"\",\"27\":[\"393\"],\"89\":\"\"}}', '2016-01-05 19:15:36', '2016-01-05 19:15:36', 'cc87b4b3-693e-44db-b840-e30b3b7d1247'),
