 ('749', '355', '4', '150', 'en_us', '9', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"204\",\"title\":\"Library & Information Science Website\",\"slug\":\"school-of-library-information-science\",\"postDate\":1451580660,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"117\":[\"400\"],\"61\":[\"120\",\"146\",\"423\",\"435\",\"442\"],\"9\":\"<p>IdeaBase took on the research, design and development for the School of Library & Information Science over a nine-month period, launching in January 2015.&nbsp;The website features a custom, responsive design template, research-backed content and navigation and was built in Drupal according to Kent State University\\u2019s Web standards.<\\/p>\",\"148\":\"\",\"46\":[\"354\"],\"161\":\"\",\"88\":[\"177\",\"175\"],\"104\":\"http:\\/\\/www.kent.edu\\/slis\",\"162\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-09 05:42:54', '2016-02-09 05:42:54', 'cc3a5918-8bfe-4803-935d-044728e275de'),
 ('750', '149', '3', '150', 'en_us', '7', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"87\",\"title\":\"Larrie King\",\"slug\":\"larrie-king\",\"postDate\":1447175700,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"118\":\"\",\"6\":\"<p>Larrie King joined the faulty of the School of Visual Communication Design in 2014 after graduating from the program with an MFA. He also holds a BFA and an MA in design from Northwestern State University, where he taught in the design program prior to attending Kent State. Originally from Louisiana, Larrie\\u2019s creative career began in fine art. Along with teaching and practicing as a freelance designer over the years, he has also exhibited work as a painter and illustrator.<\\/p><p>Larrie\\u2019s areas of expertise include print design, identity development and branding design, and research. He recently presented research from his graduate studies at the 9th Annual International Design Principles and Practiced Conference, and continues to work with global organizations like Lifewater International.<\\/p><p>As Creative Director of the award-winning Glyphix Studio, Larrie works closely with the School of VCD\\u2019s top performing students, guiding them to create design solutions for organizations like The Veale Foundation, Portage Parks District, Schneller, and Kent State University. He also serves as the school\\u2019s internship coordinator, forging relationships with local and regional studios and business owners who provide our students with competitive internship and employment opportunities.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"77\":\"MFA in Visual Communication Design, Kent State University, MA in Design, Northwestern State University, BFA in Design, Northwestern State University\",\"4\":\"lking@ideabasekent.com\",\"148\":\"\",\"115\":\"Larrie\",\"26\":[\"5\"],\"3\":\"Creative Director, Glyphix\",\"114\":\"King\",\"5\":\"330.672.7300\",\"27\":[\"242\"],\"89\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-09 06:04:42', '2016-02-09 06:04:42', '82a6b367-650a-4cdb-bfc9-4afc6ce93204'),
 ('751', '149', '3', '150', 'en_us', '8', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"87\",\"title\":\"Larrie King\",\"slug\":\"larrie-king\",\"postDate\":1447175700,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"118\":\"\",\"6\":\"<p>Larrie King joined the faulty of the School of Visual Communication Design in 2014 after graduating from the program with an MFA. He also holds a BFA and an MA in design from Northwestern State University, where he taught in the design program prior to attending Kent State. Originally from Louisiana, Larrie\\u2019s creative career began in fine art. Along with teaching and practicing as a freelance designer over the years, he has also exhibited work as a painter and illustrator.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Larrie\\u2019s areas of expertise include print design, identity development and branding design, and research. He recently presented research from his graduate studies at the 9th Annual International Design Principles and Practiced Conference, and continues to work with global organizations like Lifewater International.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>As Creative Director of the award-winning Glyphix Studio, Larrie works closely with the School of VCD\\u2019s top performing students, guiding them to create design solutions for organizations like The Veale Foundation, Portage Parks District, Schneller, and Kent State University. He also serves as the school\\u2019s internship coordinator, forging relationships with local and regional studios and business owners who provide our students with competitive internship and employment opportunities.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"77\":\"MFA in Visual Communication Design, Kent State University, MA in Design, Northwestern State University, BFA in Design, Northwestern State University\",\"4\":\"lking@ideabasekent.com\",\"148\":\"\",\"115\":\"Larrie\",\"26\":[\"5\"],\"3\":\"Creative Director, Glyphix\",\"114\":\"King\",\"5\":\"330.672.7300\",\"27\":[\"242\"],\"89\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"staffSocName\",\"enabled\":\