tent well for small-screen devices. &nbsp;We wanted a place where we were excited to send clients to review our work.\\r\\n<\\/li><li>Our content management system and theme, which was bundled with many third party plugins and a less-than-ideal structured content workflow\\r\\n<\\/li><li>Slow performance, due to the large amount of JavaScript plugins and non-effective CDN use\\r\\n<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>While we could have attempted to restructure and update the existing system and theme, we felt the challenge to be worthwhile, allowing us to try new technologies and processes while developing a site that could be shown to clients as an example of what\\u2019s possible.<\\/p>\"}},\"890\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>Business Needs, Competitive Analysis and Brand Research<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We started the process by meeting as a team (this was easy, since we were also essentially the clients), to make a list of business needs for the website. &nbsp;This helped establish design goals. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We also identified a list of competitors and aspirational websites. &nbsp;We were sure to include both local and nationally-known agencies, with a focus on agencies that concentrate on user research, an area we wanted to promote more in general. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Our User Experience Designer, Callie, analyzed our competitor websites (as well as our current website) and compared messaging and layout styles across each.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\\"Unlike the majority of our projects in which we are immersing ourselves into our clients\' business goals, branding and vocabulary, for the IdeaBase redesign, we needed to take a step back,\\\"&nbsp;Callie said. &nbsp;\\\"To make sure that our design and development efforts weren\'t clouded by our own biases, we decided to kick-off our redesign with a round of competitive research.\\\"<br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>At the same time, our Account Managers reached out to a few past clients and student employees by phone to get their feedback on proposed messaging and calls to action. &nbsp;The clients\\u2019 feedback directly helped us write content that felt like IdeaBase and no one else. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Our research helped us organize our services into the 3 themes Discover, Design and Refine and develop the \\u201cLet\\u2019s Make Something Great Together\\u201d call to action.<\\/p>\"}},\"901\":{\"type\":\"pullQuote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"pullQuote\":\"I developed a style guide that more clearly defined our brand and voice in a way that resonated with our industry and our mission.\",\"pullQuoteAuthor\":\"Callie, User Experience Designer\"}},\"891\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>Content Strategy and Sketching<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>As we were finishing up the brand research, Callie was already off to work collaborating with me on an information architecture that fit our content goals, with simplicity in mind. &nbsp;We used Google Drive to divide content into sections, and write\\/edit the content. &nbsp;Existing content came from many places, including our current website, promotional materials and viewbook and videos. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We took the best content out of each, threw out content that didn\\u2019t meet our goals and developed new content to fill in the gaps. &nbsp;Photos, which often get forgotten in the content process, were taken by Chris (headshots), Todd (headshots and environmental photos) and Mario (project photos).<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>At the end, we had a rough content prototype built in Google Drive, even before a single design concept had been developed. &nbsp;We continued to modify content throughout the entire project.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>As Callie worked on refining the content, I worked on sketching out the general user flows and mobile-first content layouts on paper. &nbsp;Callie turned these sketches into more polished wireframes later.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Callie described the&nbsp;process:&nbsp;\\\"I developed a style guide that more clearly defined our brand and voice in a way that resonated with our industry and our mission. Once the style guide was refined, I led the content strategy efforts, modifying existing content to align with our style guide. I used this content to generate mobile-first wireframes to prioritize content delivery across all channels.\\\"<\\/p>\"}},\"899\":{\"type\":\"pullQuote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"pullQuote\":\"I was able to get a better understanding of how building a full site from scratch really works.\",\"pullQuoteAuthor\":\"John, Designer\"}},\"892\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>Design and Development<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>John, our visual designer didn\\u2019t have to wait for all of the content to get started. &nbsp;After reviewing the rough sketches and competitive research, he developed a set of style tiles that showed our proposed typography, color and style choices for the website. &nbsp;The style tiles still today closely match the website style. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Having just learned HTML and CSS, John quickly turned the static style tiles into an HTML\\/CSS style prototype so that we could see the styles in the browser and make revisions from there. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>After we had decided on our visual direction, John began developing static mockups week-by-week of different interface components, starting with the home page components and then working through services, profiles, blog posts and more. &nbsp;John also produced some really cool, custom-drawn vector graphics that are used throughout the website. &nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"898\":{\"type\":\"image\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"897\"]}},\"900\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>At the end of each day, John would post a rough Illustrator mockup to Basecamp, which I added to our HTML\\/CSS\\/PHP prototype repository hosted on GitHub. &nbsp;This continuous design\\/development helped us immediately see how the design would scale in the browser and make changes as needed. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We ended up with a working prototype that represented the various templates to be used on the website. &nbsp;This was helpful when our other User Experience Designer, Chris, began usability testing the prototype (in three rounds). &nbsp;We had something that they could actually use and test on multiple devices, even if it wasn\\u2019t fully complete.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>John said that \\\"after working on the website closely with Chris for several weeks, I was able to get a better understanding of how building a full site from scratch really works. One of the benefits of this team effort was that Chris, as a developer, has a lot of knowledge about design \\u2013 and I, as a designer, have a bit of experience in developing. This strengthened our communication during the process as we transitioned my page patterns from Adobe Illustrator into functioning web pages in HTML and CSS.\\\"<\\/p>\"}},\"896\":{\"type\":\"pullQuote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"pullQuote\":\"I enjoyed working with a new content management system, and fully developing a backend for a site.\",\"pullQuoteAuthor\":\"Reilly, Web Developer\"}},\"893\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>Content Management System<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>As the content was being finalized (remember that this isn\\u2019t a waterfall process!), Reilly our web developer began mapping out the content into fields and content types. &nbsp;We took a chance and selected the relatively new Craft CMS as our content management system, because of its design flexibility and intuitive templating language. &nbsp;Craft gives the designers and developers absolute control over every part of the website implementation (there are no \\u201cthemes\\u201d) and provides a great, structured editing experience on the front-end. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>As I developed the front-end prototype templates, Reilly used that raw HTML code to integrate into the actual CMS templates. &nbsp;Since our CSS and JavaScript assets were shared between both the development and production environments, we saw changes to the CMS templates instantly!<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Reilly had this to say about working with Craft:&nbsp;\\\"I enjoyed working with a new content management system, and fully developing a backend for a site from scratch.&nbsp;In the future, I think Craft will become a very simple, easy to use CMS that is a good thing to have on a resume.\\\"<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Once Craft was in a state ready for content entry, the entire team worked together to build out the site content and pages, including migrating all of our work, blog posts and staff profiles to the new system.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>I also worked to improve performance on the site, setting up caching via CloudFlare, compressing and minifying assets and implementing responsive images to reduce mobile data use.<\\/p>\"}},\"894\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>Our End Result<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We launched the website on Valentine\\u2019s Day 2016. &nbsp;To build up excitement for the launch, our designer Rachel developed some great social media teasers. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The entire redesign process took about 5 months from beginning to end. &nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"895\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>For the Future<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>A redesigned website is only as good as its maintenance plan. &nbsp;As a team, we worked to develop better content governance roles, with plans on how to add new work, new student staff members and blog posts. &nbsp;We\\u2019re also now in the process of turning all of our brand assets and content guidelines into an online IdeaBase Style Guide, which will live alongside our website in Craft. &nbsp;The Style Guide will help keep content and design elements consistent across all of our communications materials. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We\\u2019re so excited for the future of IdeaBase and what the website, while only a small part of what we do, will allow us to do for future clients. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>A big thank you to the core project team, as well as the entire IdeaBase staff, including Kristin Dowling and Quintin Steele, who helped act as our \\u201cclients\\u201d and keep the project on track. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>View the Project Details and Team Members &gt;<br><\\/p>\"}}},\"156\":[\"607\",\"625\"],\"11\":\"<p>The term \\u201credesign\\u201d is throw around continuously in any creative agency setting. &nbsp;But what is a redesign really? &nbsp;Is it simply updating the current website design to be more aesthetically pleasing, or does the \\u201cre\\u201d prefix indicate starting over from scratch?<\\/p>\",\"148\":\"\",\"49\":[\"123\"]}}', '2016-02-12 17:39:58', '2016-02-12 17:39:58', '0666d7a8-b83d-4c6a-b782-2397258031e2'),
 ('959', '888', '5', '150', 'en_us', '15', '', '{\"typeId\":\"5\",\"authorId\":\"150\",\"title\":\"Redesigning the IdeaBase Website from the Ground Up\",\"slug\":\"redesigning-the-ideabase-website-from-the-ground-up\",\"postDate\":1455296580,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":0,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"60\":[\"120\"],\"92\":\"\",\"142\":{\"889\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>In my perspective, an organization should undergo a redesign for the right reasons. &nbsp;The content doesn\\u2019t answer our users\\u2019 questions, the design is built from a desktop-first perspective and the backend architecture has become a mess of spaghetti code.<br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In this case, we faced a similar decision with our own internal agency website for IdeaBase. &nbsp;After 5 years in a WordPress-powered site, using a modified purchased theme, with few content improvements over the years, was it time to redesign from the ground up? &nbsp;How would we counsel clients in the same situation?<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In the end, our team decided to begin in Summer 2015 for a redesign due to:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Our messaging and branding, which had become disjointed and lacked a clear, voice. \\r\\n<\\/li><li>Our design and layout, which appeared outdated, without a good call to action. &nbsp;The design, while responsive, did not scale or prioritize content well for small-screen devices. &nbsp;We wanted a place where we were excited to send clients to review our work.\\r\\n<\\/li><li>Our content management system and theme, which was bundled with many third party plugins and a less-than-ideal structured content workflow\\r\\n<\\/li><li>Slow performance, due to the large amount of JavaScript plugins and non-effective CDN use\\r\\n<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>While we could have attempted to restructure and update the existing system and theme, we felt the challenge to be worthwhile, allowing us to try new technologies and processes while developing a site that could be shown to clients as an example of what\\u2019s possible.<\\/p>\"}},\"890\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>Business Needs, Competitive Analysis and Brand Research<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We started the process by meeting as a team (this was easy, since we were also essentially the clients), to make a list of business needs for the website. &nbsp;This helped establish design goals. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We also identified a list of competitors and aspirational websites. &nbsp;We were sure to include both local and nationally-known agencies, with a focus on agencies that concentrate on user research, an area we wanted to promote more in general. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Our User Experience Designer, Callie, analyzed our competitor websites (as well as our current website) and compared messaging and layout styles across each.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\\"Unlike the majority of our projects in which we are immersing ourselves into our clients\' business goals, branding and vocabulary, for the IdeaBase redesign, we needed to take a step back,\\\"&nbsp;Callie said. &nbsp;\\\"To make sure that our design and development efforts weren\'t clouded by our own biases, we decided to kick-off our redesign with a round of competitive research.\\\"<br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>At the same time, our Account Managers reached out to a few past clients and student employees by phone to get their feedback on proposed messaging and calls to action. &nbsp;The clients\\u2019 feedback directly helped us write content that felt like IdeaBase and no one else. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Our research helped us organize our services into the 3 themes Discover, Design and Refine and develop the \\u201cLet\\u2019s Make Something Great Together\\u201d call to action.<\\/p>\"}},\"901\":{\"type\":\"pullQuote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"pullQuote\":\"I developed a style guide that more clearly defined our brand and voice in a way that resonated with our industry and our mission.\",\"pullQuoteAuthor\":\"Callie, User Experience Designer\"}},\"891\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>Content Strategy and Sketching<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>As we were finishing up the brand research, Callie was already off to work collaborating with me on an information architecture that fit our content goals, with simplicity in mind. &nbsp;We used Google Drive to divide content into sections, and write\\/edit the content. &nbsp;Existing content came from many places, including our current website, promotional materials and viewbook and videos. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We took the best content out of each, threw out content that didn\\u2019t meet our goals and developed new content to fill in the gaps. &nbsp;Photos, which often get forgotten in the content process, were taken by Chris (headshots), Todd (headshots and environmental photos) and Mario (project photos).<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>At the end, we had a rough content prototype built in Google Drive, even before a single design concept had been developed. &nbsp;We continued to modify content throughout the entire project.<\\/p>\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"image\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"902\"]}},\"new1\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>As Callie worked on refining the content, I worked on sketching out the general user flows and mobile-first content layouts on paper. &nbsp;Callie turned these sketches into more polished wireframes later.<\\/p><p>Callie described the&nbsp;process:&nbsp;\\\"I developed a style guide that more clearly defined our brand and voice in a way that resonated with our industry and our mission. Once the style guide was refined, I led the content strategy efforts, modifying existing content to align with our style guide. I used this content to generate mobile-first wireframes to prioritize content delivery across all channels.\\\"<\\/p>\"}},\"899\":{\"type\":\"pullQuote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"pullQuote\":\"I was able to get a better understanding of how building a full site from scratch really works.\",\"pullQuoteAuthor\":\"John, Designer\"}},\"892\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>Design and Development<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>John, our visual designer didn\\u2019t have to wait for all of the content to get started. &nbsp;After reviewing the rough sketches and competitive research, he developed a set of style tiles that showed our proposed typography, color and style choices for the website. &nbsp;The style tiles still today closely match the website style. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Having just learned HTML and CSS, John quickly turned the static style tiles into an HTML\\/CSS style prototype so that we could see the styles in the browser and make revisions from there. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>After we had decided on our visual direction, John began developing static mockups week-by-week of different interface components, starting with the home page components and then working through services, profiles, blog posts and more. &nbsp;John also produced some really cool, custom-drawn vector graphics that are used throughout the website. &nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"898\":{\"type\":\"image\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"897\"]}},\"900\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>At the end of each day, John would post a rough Illustrator mockup to Basecamp, which I added to our HTML\\/CSS\\/PHP prototype repository hosted on GitHub. &nbsp;This continuous design\\/development helped us immediately see how the design would scale in the browser and make changes as needed. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We ended up with a working prototype that represented the various templates to be used on the website. &nbsp;This was helpful when our other User Experience Designer, Chris, began usability testing the prototype (in three rounds). &nbsp;We had something that they could actually use and test on multiple devices, even if it wasn\\u2019t fully complete.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>John said that \\\"after working on the website closely with Chris for several weeks, I was able to get a better understanding of how building a full site from scratch really works. One of the benefits of this team effort was that Chris, as a developer, has a lot of knowledge about design \\u2013 and I, as a designer, have a bit of experience in developing. This strengthened our communication during the process as we transitioned my page patterns from Adobe Illustrator into functioning web pages in HTML and CSS.\\\"<\\/p>\"}},\"896\":{\"type\":\"pullQuote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"pullQuote\":\"I enjoyed working with a new content management system, and fully developing a backend for a site.\",\"pullQuoteAuthor\":\"Reilly, Web Developer\"}},\"893\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>Content Management System<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>As the content was being finalized (remember that this isn\\u2019t a waterfall process!), Reilly our web developer began mapping out the content into fields and content types. &nbsp;We took a chance and selected the relatively new Craft CMS as our content management system, because of its design flexibility and intuitive templating language. &nbsp;Craft gives the designers and developers absolute control over every part of the website implementation (there are no \\u201cthemes\\u201d) and provides a great, structured editing experience on the front-end. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>As I developed the front-end prototype templates, Reilly used that raw HTML code to integrate into the actual CMS templates. &nbsp;Since our CSS and JavaScript assets were shared between both the development and production environments, we saw changes to the CMS templates instantly!<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Reilly had this to say about working with Craft:&nbsp;\\\"I enjoyed working with a new content management system, and fully developing a backend for a site from scratch.&nbsp;In the future, I think Craft will become a very simple, easy to use CMS that is a good thing to have on a resume.\\\"<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Once Craft was in a state ready for content entry, the entire team worked together to build out the site content and pages, including migrating all of our work, blog posts and staff profiles to the new system.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>I also worked to improve performance on the site, setting up caching via CloudFlare, compressing and minifying assets and implementing responsive images to reduce mobile data use.<\\/p>\"}},\"894\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>Our End Result<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We launched the website on Valentine\\u2019s Day 2016. &nbsp;To build up excitement for the launch, our designer Rachel developed some great social media teasers. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The entire redesign process took about 5 months from beginning to end. &nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"895\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>For the Future<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>A redesigned website is only as good as its maintenance plan. &nbsp;As a team, we worked to develop better content governance roles, with plans on how to add new work, new student staff members and blog posts. &nbsp;We\\u2019re also now in the process of turning all of our brand assets and content guidelines into an online IdeaBase Style Guide, which will live alongside our website in Craft. &nbsp;The Style Guide will help keep content and design elements consistent across all of our communications materials. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We\\u2019re so excited for the future of IdeaBase and what the website, while only a small part of what we do, will allow us to do for future clients. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>A big thank you to the core project team, as well as the entire IdeaBase staff, including Kristin Dowling and Quintin Steele, who helped act as our \\u201cclients\\u201d and keep the project on track. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>View the Project Details and Team Members &gt;<br><\\/p>\"}}},\"156\":[\"607\",\"625\"],\"11\":\"<p>The term \\u201credesign\\u201d is throw around continuously in any creative agency setting. &nbsp;But what is a redesign really? &nbsp;Is it simply updating the current website design to be more aesthetically pleasing, or does the \\u201cre\\u201d prefix indicate starting over from scratch?<\\/p>\",\"148\":\"\",\"49\":[\"123\"]}}', '2016-02-12 17:44:04', '2016-02-12 17:44:04', 'eeb6b794-dc89-47a7-ae93-1df550f2dfee'),
 ('960', '109', '12', '150', 'en_us', '35', '', '{\"typeId\":\"12\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Services\",\"slug\":\"process-index\",\"postDate\":1453923350,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"155\":[\"591\"],\"148\":\"Let our suite of user research, design and testing services guide your product development; we offer everything from competitive analysis to graphic and Web design to eyetracking and usability testing in our very own UX Testing Lab.\",\"37\":[\"829\"],\"106\":\"<p>While our unique business model allows us to deliver high-quality products at an affordable cost, there\\u2019s no \\u201cone size fits all\\u201d when it comes to individual client needs. We work with our clients upfront to define goals and timelines to ensure that we deliver a great end&nbsp;product within the project\\u2019s constraints. Together, we\\u2019ll plan and build something great, and it won\\u2019t break the bank.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Contact us today and we\'ll put together a customized proposal&nbsp;for your next project.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"107\":\"Sounds great, how much does it cost?\",\"79\":\"<p>We support our clients\\u2019 design initiatives from the early discovery phase through implementation (or anywhere in between). Whether you\\u2019re laying the foundation for your product\\u2019s success, or building out and refining your design, we\\u2019re here to help. And we do all of this right here locally from our <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.ideabasekent.com\\/prod\\/about#entry:492:url\\\">fabulous office space<\\/a> in downtown Kent.<br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n<\\/p>\",\"42\":\"Design services tailored to you\",\"94\":{\"183\":{\"type\":\"processMatrix\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"homeProcessName\":\"Discover\",\"homeProcessDescription\":\"<p>Discover who your users are and what they are looking for in your product.<\\/p>\",\"homeProcessExampleTable\":[{\"col1\":\"User Interviews\"},{\"col1\":\"Surveys\"},{\"col1\":\"Competitive Analysis\"},{\"col1\":\"Persona Development\"},{\"col1\":\"Focus Groups\"},{\"col1\":\"Heuristics \"}],\"icon1\":[\"252\"],\"icon2\":[\"253\"],\"icon3\":[\"248\"],\"icon4\":[\"257\"],\"homepageIcon\":[\"245\"],\"homepageDescription\":\"<p>Our targeted user research methods empower you to more effectively address your users\'&nbsp;needs.<\\/p>\"}},\"184\":{\"type\":\"processMatrix\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"homeProcessName\":\"Design\",\"homeProcessDescription\":\"<p>Design a creative product that delivers on user and business needs.<\\/p>\",\"homeProcessExampleTable\":[{\"col1\":\"Print & Graphic Design\"},{\"col1\":\"Video Production\"},{\"col1\":\"Email Marketing\"},{\"col1\":\"Web Design & Development\"},{\"col1\":\"Content Strategy\"},{\"col1\":\"Environmental Design\"},{\"col1\":\"Brand Identity \"},{\"col1\":\"Social Media Campaigns\"}],\"icon1\":[\"249\"],\"icon2\":[\"254\"],\"icon3\":[\"256\"],\"icon4\":[\"246\"],\"homepageIcon\":[\"244\"],\"homepageDescription\":\"<p>Our design strategies, whether through print, video or web, deliver custom solutions that&nbsp;promote both business and customer needs.<\\/p>\"}},\"185\":{\"type\":\"processMatrix\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"homeProcessName\":\"Refine\",\"homeProcessDescription\":\"<p>Refine an existing product with our advanced testing process.<\\/p>\",\"homeProcessExampleTable\":[{\"col1\":\"In-Person Usability Testing\"},{\"col1\":\"Remote Usability Testing\"},{\"col1\":\"Device & Performance Testing\"},{\"col1\":\"Eyetracking Usability \"}],\"icon1\":[\"247\"],\"icon2\":[\"250\"],\"icon3\":[\"251\"],\"icon4\":[\"255\"],\"homepageIcon\":[\"258\"],\"homepageDescription\":\"<p>Our advanced usability testing tools, including eye tracking, allow you to evaluate the effectiveness of design solutions.<\\/p>\"}}},\"108\":\"More about our UX Testing Lab\",\"80\":\"<p>We can test the performance and usability of your product on various devices in our User Experience Testing Lab. This is a great resource to ensure that your product translates across all platforms.\\r\\n<\\/p>\"}}', '2016-02-12 17:47:42', '2016-02-12 17:47:42', 'faf74106-c281-4350-9873-dc1bb378d74e'),
 ('961', '108', '11', '150', 'en_us', '30', '', '{\"typeId\":\"11\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"People\",\"slug\":\"staff-profile-index\",\"postDate\":1445610228,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"155\":[\"592\"],\"39\":\"<p>We hire only the best students from Kent State\'s communication&nbsp;programs. Our students work under the guidance of full-time staff members from the <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.kent.edu\\/cci\\\">College of Communication of Information<\\/a> and a <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.ideabasekent.com\\/prod\\/people\\/board#entry:539:url\\\">professional \\/&nbsp;faculty&nbsp;advisory board<\\/a>, ensuring we produce the highest quality products for our clients. &nbsp;Our commitment to real-world experience ensures our&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.ideabasekent.com\\/prod\\/people\\/alumni#entry:540:url\\\">numerous alumni<\\/a>&nbsp;are poised for real-world success upon graduation.<\\/p>\",\"148\":\"We hire only the best students from Kent State\'s design, advertising, user experience, computer science and electronic media programs. Our student employees get to put their design skills to the test, build their resumes and jumpstart their careers.\",\"37\":[\"837\"],\"38\":\"People Passionate about Design\",\"45\":\"\",\"41\":\"We empower our student employees to imagine, create and deliver quality designs while gaining real-world experience on client-facing projects. Our student employees get to put their design skills to the test, build their resumes and jumpstart their careers.\",\"58\":[\"524\"],\"40\":\"Work for IdeaBase\"}}', '2016-02-12 17:48:05', '2016-02-12 17:48:05', '9717d99e-0a35-44ea-ac20-02712e17ad4f'),
 ('962', '148', '15', '150', 'en_us', '26', '', '{\"typeId\":\"15\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Work\",\"slug\":\"projects-homepage\",\"postDate\":1453923363,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"155\":[\"590\"],\"71\":\"How we\'re making a difference\",\"72\":\"<p>We make a positive impact on your design and our student designers by taking the time to build right. Read case studies from our past projects to see for yourself.<\\/p>\",\"109\":\"IdeaBase Classroom Experiences\",\"74\":\"<p>At IdeaBase, we want our student employees to succeed. That\\u2019s why we partner with Glyphix to teach the next generation through studio experiences. Our students develop and exercise project-based skills in marketing, design, research and more. Additionally, our Responsive Web Design class ensures the next generation of designers and developers understand how to create highly functional and usable websites.<\\/p>\",\"73\":\"Helping our students succeed\",\"148\":\"We\'re not just transforming our clients\' products and brands with our award-winning design solutions; we\'re transforming our student employees by giving them the chance to work directly with clients, managing all stages of design production.\",\"37\":[\"833\"],\"110\":\"See All Work\",\"69\":\"Our Work Speaks for Itself\",\"70\":\"<p>We deliver awarding-winning, quality design solutions that transform our clients\\u2019 products and brands. In turn, our talented students get the chance to work directly with clients, developing proposals, managing projects and handling all stages of design production.<\\/p>\"}}', '2016-02-12 17:48:27', '2016-02-12 17:48:27', '3deaa531-2e5f-479a-9707-0501452361e9');
