 ('59', '698', 'en_us', '<ol><li>E. Main Street (front entrance) &nbsp;- metered parking (free on weekdays after 5 p.m. and on weekends)</li><li>Erie Street (back entrance) - metered parking&nbsp;(free on weekdays after 5 p.m. and on weekends)</li><li>Hourly parking&nbsp;in the <a href=\"http://www.mainstreetkent.org/parking-info/4556263055\" target=\"_blank\">PARTA parking garage</a> on S. Depeyster St.</li><li>On W. Main St. bridge that crosses the river (Free&nbsp;2 hour increments)</li><li>Lot behind the Kent Stage (Columbus Street) in two hour increments (Free)</li><li>Franklin Ave, near Rt. 59 overpass (Free)</li><li>Lot on the corner of W.&nbsp;College Ave. and Franklin Ave. (Free)</li><li>Large lot behind Panini\'s (free on weekends and weekdays after 5 p.m. only)</li></ol>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-06 07:36:57', '2016-02-10 02:40:50', 'be3184bf-0f31-4ebe-9b81-188d09f42cc7');
INSERT INTO `craft_matrixcontent_blogpostcontent` (`id`, `elementId`, `locale`, `field_text_text`, `field_video_videoUrl`, `field_pullQuote_pullQuote`, `field_pullQuote_pullQuoteAuthor`, `dateCreated`, `dateUpdated`, `uid`) VALUES
 ('1', '609', 'en_us', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-04 21:06:10', '2016-02-12 17:01:50', '6eacb8ce-f76a-4df2-951c-ef3deea04114'),
 ('2', '889', 'en_us', '<p>In my perspective, an organization should undergo a redesign for the right reasons. &nbsp;The content doesnt answer our users questions, the design is built from a desktop-first perspective and the backend architecture has become a mess of spaghetti code.<br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>In this case, we faced a similar decision with our own internal agency website for IdeaBase. &nbsp;After 5 years in a WordPress-powered site, using a modified purchased theme, with few content improvements over the years, was it time to redesign from the ground up? &nbsp;How would we counsel clients in the same situation?</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>In the end, our team decided to begin in Summer 2015 for a redesign due to:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Our messaging and branding, which had become disjointed and lacked a clear, voice. \r\n</li><li>Our design and layout, which appeared outdated, without a good call to action. &nbsp;The design, while responsive, did not scale or prioritize content well for small-screen devices. &nbsp;We wanted a place where we were excited to send clients to review our work.\r\n</li><li>Our content management system and theme, which was bundled with many third party plugins and a less-than-ideal structured content workflow\r\n</li><li>Slow performance, due to the large amount of JavaScript plugins and non-effective CDN use\r\n</li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>While we could have attempted to restructure and update the existing system and theme, we felt the challenge to be worthwhile, allowing us to try new technologies and processes while developing a site that could be shown to clients as an example of whats possible.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-12 17:09:15', '2016-02-12 17:44:04', '9ea72129-248a-4eb9-98e8-4bd91c109ed9'),
 ('3', '890', 'en_us', '<h2>Business Needs, Competitive Analysis and Brand Research</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>We started the process by meeting as a team (this was easy, since we were also essentially the clients), to make a list of business needs for the website. &nbsp;This helped establish design goals. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>We also identified a list of competitors and aspirational websites. &nbsp;We were sure to include both local and nationally-known agencies, with a focus on agencies that concentrate on user research, an area we wanted to promote more in general. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Our User Experience Designer, Callie, analyzed our competitor websites (as well as our current website) and compared messaging and layout styles across each.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\"Unlike the majority of our projects in which we are immersing ourselves into our clients\' business goals, branding and vocabulary, for the IdeaBase redesign, we needed to take a step back,\"&nbsp;Callie said. &nbsp;\"To make sure that our design and development efforts weren\'t clouded by our own biases, we decided to kick-off our redesign with a round of competitive research.\"<br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>At the same time, our Account Managers reached out to a few past clients and student employees by phone to get their feedback on proposed messaging and calls to action. &nbsp;The clients feedback directly helped us write content that felt like IdeaBase and no one else. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Our research helped us organize our services into the 3 themes Discover, Design and Refine and develop the Lets Make Something Great Together call to action.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-12 17:09:15', '2016-02-12 17:44:04', '9a36a96e-43b4-4dd3-b1dd-61c3061662e8'),
 ('4', '891', 'en_us', '<h2>Content Strategy and Sketching</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As we were finishing up the brand research, Callie was already off to work collaborating with me on an information architecture that fit our content goals, with simplicity in mind. &nbsp;We used Google Drive to divide content into sections, and write/edit the content. &nbsp;Existing content came from many places, including our current website, promotional materials and viewbook and videos. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>We took the best content out of each, threw out content that didnt meet our goals and developed new content to fill in the gaps. &nbsp;Photos, which often get forgotten in the content process, were taken by Chris (headshots), Todd (headshots and environmental photos) and Mario (project photos).</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>At the end, we had a rough content prototype built in Google Drive, even before a single design concept had been developed. &nbsp;We continued to modify content throughout the entire project.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-12 17:09:15', '2016-02-12 17:44:04', 'abe7d7ac-073d-40bd-8a42-4df416f514b0'),
 ('5', '892', 'en_us', '<h2>Design and Development</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>John, our visual designer didnt have to wait for all of the content to get started. &nbsp;After reviewing the rough sketches and competitive research, he developed a set of style tiles that showed our proposed typography, color and style choices for the website. &nbsp;The style tiles still today closely match the website style. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Having just learned HTML and CSS, John quickly turned the static style tiles into an HTML/CSS style prototype so that we could see the styles in the browser and make revisions from there. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>After we had decided on our visual direction, John began developing static mockups week-by-week of different interface components, starting with the home page components and then working through services, profiles, blog posts and more. &nbsp;John also produced some really cool, custom-drawn vector graphics that are used throughout the website. &nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-12 17:09:15', '2016-02-12 17:44:04', '6ead2c44-aeeb-4444-99ac-624e8fc07cff'),
 ('6', '893', 'en_us', '<h2>Content Management System</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As the content was being finalized (remember that this isnt a waterfall process!), Reilly our web developer began mapping out the content into fields and content types. &nbsp;We took a chance and selected the relatively new Craft CMS as our content management system, because of its design flexibility and intuitive templating language. &nbsp;Craft gives the designers and developers absolute control over every part of the website implementation (there are no themes) and provides a great, structured editing experience on the front-end. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>As I developed the front-end prototype templates, Reilly used that raw HTML code to integrate into the actual CMS templates. &nbsp;Since our CSS and JavaScript assets were shared between both the development and production environments, we saw changes to the CMS templates instantly!</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Reilly had this to say about working with Craft:&nbsp;\"I enjoyed working with a new content management system, and fully developing a backend for a site from scratch.&nbsp;In the future, I think Craft will become a very simple, easy to use CMS that is a good thing to have on a resume.\"</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Once Craft was in a state ready for content entry, the entire team worked together to build out the site content and pages, including migrating all of our work, blog posts and staff profiles to the new system.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>I also worked to improve performance on the site, setting up caching via CloudFlare, compressing and minifying assets and implementing responsive images to reduce mobile data use.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-12 17:09:15', '2016-02-12 17:44:04', '6c89b49b-e376-47c1-9840-bc5a62e38831'),
 ('7', '894', 'en_us', '<h2>Our End Result</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>We launched the website on Valentines Day 2016. &nbsp;To build up excitement for the launch, our designer Rachel developed some great social media teasers. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>The entire redesign process took about 5 months from beginning to end. &nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-12 17:09:15', '2016-02-12 17:44:04', '2739fea8-ca4c-4bbf-918f-8242cca5e50d'),
 ('8', '895', 'en_us', '<h2>For the Future</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A redesigned website is only as good as its maintenance plan. &nbsp;As a team, we worked to develop better content governance roles, with plans on how to add new work, new student staff members and blog posts. &nbsp;Were also now in the process of turning all of our brand assets and content guidelines into an online IdeaBase Style Guide, which will live alongside our website in Craft. &nbsp;The Style Guide will help keep content and design elements consistent across all of our communications materials. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Were so excited for the future of IdeaBase and what the website, while only a small part of what we do, will allow us to do for future clients. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>A big thank you to the core project team, as well as the entire IdeaBase staff, including Kristin Dowling and Quintin Steele, who helped act as our clients and keep the project on track. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>View the Project Details and Team Members &gt;<br></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-12 17:09:15', '2016-02-12 17:44:04', 'c0b6cd37-ccc8-41c6-9b3d-228dc1f57e6a'),
 ('9', '896', 'en_us', NULL, NULL, 'I enjoyed working with a new content management system, and fully developing a backend for a site.', 'Reilly, Web Developer', '2016-02-12 17:21:45', '2016-02-12 17:44:04', 'e76c9710-947d-46e2-a523-88342c8b043f'),
 ('10', '898', 'en_us', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-12 17:23:07', '2016-02-12 17:44:04', '0718f16d-f7f7-4c49-bfd4-2f7d8abf6bc3'),
 ('11', '899', 'en_us', NULL, NULL, 'I was able to get a better understanding of how building a full site from scratch really works.', 'John, Designer', '2016-02-12 17:31:05', '2016-02-12 17:44:04', '03302ba2-e6c4-4540-9038-e8c91e35c67d'),
 ('12', '900', 'en_us', '<p>At the end of each day, John would post a rough Illustrator mockup to Basecamp, which I added to our HTML/CSS/PHP prototype repository hosted on GitHub. &nbsp;This continuous design/development helped us immediately see how the design would scale in the browser and make changes as needed. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We ended up with a working prototype that represented the various templates to be used on the website. &nbsp;This was helpful when our other User Experience Designer, Chris, began usability testing the prototype (in three rounds). &nbsp;We had something that they could actually use and test on multiple devices, even if it wasnt fully complete.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>John said that \"after working on the website closely with Chris for several weeks, I was able to get a better understanding of how building a full site from scratch really works. One of the benefits of this team effort was that Chris, as a developer, has a lot of knowledge about design  and I, as a designer, have a bit of experience in developing. This strengthened our communication during the process as we transitioned my page patterns from Adobe Illustrator into functioning web pages in HTML and CSS.\"</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-12 17:32:08', '2016-02-12 17:44:04', 'eeb41680-7da4-46c4-88c3-d18b829c6f45'),
 ('13', '901', 'en_us', NULL, NULL, 'I developed a style guide that more clearly defined our brand and voice in a way that resonated with our industry and our mission.', 'Callie, User Experience Designer', '2016-02-12 17:37:07', '2016-02-12 17:44:04', '83bc85ed-2a47-4f49-8fc6-bdc90e0519db'),
 ('14', '903', 'en_us', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-12 17:44:04', '2016-02-12 17:44:04', '54b10ca5-a77d-4efa-a1f4-edc40c0d82ed'),
 ('15', '904', 'en_us', '<p>As Callie worked on refining the content, I worked on sketching out the general user flows and mobile-first content layouts on paper. &nbsp;Callie turned these sketches into more polished wireframes later.</p><p>Callie described the&nbsp;process:&nbsp;\"I developed a style guide that more clearly defined our brand and voice in a way that resonated with our industry and our mission. Once the style guide was refined, I led the content strategy efforts, modifying existing content to align with our style guide. I used this content to generate mobile-first wireframes to prioritize content delivery across all channels.\"</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-12 17:44:04', '2016-02-12 17:44:04', '251b6c9f-d04a-47eb-a1d0-246cd1ff4ab1');
